A 3-node CockroachDB cluster has been deployed but not yet initialized.

OBSERVED STATE:
- CockroachDB pods are running but the cluster is not forming
- Pod logs show join/advertise errors when attempting to contact peer nodes

YOUR TASK:
Diagnose and fix the configuration so all 3 nodes can join.
Initialize the CockroachDB cluster so it becomes SQL-ready.

CONSTRAINTS:
- Use existing resources; do not recreate the cluster.
- No CRDs/operators/Helm.
- Insecure mode (no TLS) for this case.

HINT:
Use in-cluster tooling available in the CockroachDB pods.

GOAL:
- Cluster accepts SQL connections.
- 3 nodes are healthy and visible in cluster status.

Useful commands:
```bash
# View pod logs
kubectl -n cockroachdb logs crdb-cluster-0

# Check all pods
kubectl -n cockroachdb get pods

# Interactive SQL shell
kubectl -n cockroachdb exec -it crdb-cluster-0 -- ./cockroach sql --insecure
```
